[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer-driven test of the `curl_fuzzer_http` target triggers an [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer-detected segmentation fault in the `Curl_doh_close` function in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`lib/doh.c`. The fault arises during a read from an invalid, high memory address, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mleading to a wild-addr-read crash [0m[1;39m([0m[39mSCARINESS: [0m[1;36m20[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when running a single input [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrepeatedly.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  During an interactive fuzzing session with `curl_fuzzer_http` [0m[1;39m([0m[39musing `libfuzzer`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100[0m[39m runs, [0m[1;36m2.5[0m[39m GB RSS limit, [0m[1;36m25[0m[39m s timeout[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, AddressSanitizer reports a SEGV in [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close` at `lib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1410:30[0m[39m`. The crash stack trace indicates that the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvalid read propagates through `Curl_req_done`, `multi_done`, and the multi [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minterface, ultimately invoked by the fuzzer harness in `curl_fuzzer.cc`.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability Type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The sanitizer classifies this as a wild-addr-read [0m[1;39m([0m[39minvalid memory read[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicative of an unchecked pointer dereference leading to a segmentation fault. [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWhile the report does not explicitly label it as a use-after-free or null [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdereference, the dereference of a “high value address” suggests corruption or [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmisuse of a pointer.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key Observations  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The crash occurs inside `Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDNS-over-HTTPS cleanup[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m at line [0m[1;36m1410[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `lib/doh.c`.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer harness invokes `curl_multi_perform` via `fuzz_handle_transfer`, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexercising the multi interface and request teardown logic.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • AddressSanitizer cannot provide further heap or allocation stack details, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimplying the faulting pointer was not recently freed by a tracked allocator or that[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe metadata is out of scope.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Areas for Investigation  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. **lib/doh.c** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparticularly `Curl_doh_close` around line [0m[1;36m1410[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: examine [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer initialization and cleanup paths for DoH handles or state objects.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. **lib/request.c** [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Curl_req_done`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: trace how `doh` related structures are [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpassed into and out of request teardown.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. **lib/multi.c** [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`multi_done`, `multi_runsingle`, `curl_multi_perform`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreview the multi-handle lifecycle and error handling that leads to calling [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close`.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. **Fuzzer harness in curl_fuzzer.cc**: identify the context in which [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmulti-perform is driven and confirm the input sequence that leads to cleanup [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvocation.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis report captures the crash symptoms, relevant stack frames, and primary code [0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4322[0m[39m:                                        curl_off_t mid[0m[1;39m)[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4323[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4324[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4325[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmid >= [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4326[0m[39m:    struct Curl_easy *data;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4327[0m[39m:    struct Curl_llist_node *e;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4328[0m[39m:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4329[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mfor[0m[1;39m([0m[39me = [0m[1;35mCurl_llist_head[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&multi->process[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; e; e = [0m[1;35mCurl_node_next[0m[1;39m([0m[39me[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4330[0m[39m:      data = [0m[1;35mCurl_node_elem[0m[1;39m([0m[39me[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4331[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->mid == mid[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4332[0m[39m:        return data;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4333[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4334[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* may be in msgsent queue *[0m[35m/[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4335[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mfor[0m[1;39m([0m[39me = [0m[1;35mCurl_llist_head[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&multi->msgsent[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; e; e = [0m[1;35mCurl_node_next[0m[1;39m([0m[39me[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4336[0m[39m:      data = [0m[1;35mCurl_node_elem[0m[1;39m([0m[39me[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4337[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->mid == mid[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4338[0m[39m:        return data;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4339[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4340[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* may be in pending queue *[0m[35m/[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4341[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mfor[0m[1;39m([0m[39me = [0m[1;35mCurl_llist_head[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&multi->pending[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; e; e = [0m[1;35mCurl_node_next[0m[1;39m([0m[39me[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4342[0m[39m:      data = [0m[1;35mCurl_node_elem[0m[1;39m([0m[39me[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4343[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->mid == mid[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4344[0m[39m:        return data;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4345[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4346[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4347[0m[39m:  return NULL;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4348[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/multi.[0m[1;92mc:776[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m795[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m776:C[0m[39mURLMcode [0m[1;35mcurl_multi_remove_handle[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCURLM *m, CURL *d[0m[1;39m)[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m777[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m778[0m[39m:  struct Curl_multi *multi = m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m779[0m[39m:  struct Curl_easy *data = d;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m780[0m[39m:  bool premature;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m781[0m[39m:  struct Curl_llist_node *e;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m782[0m[39m:  CURLMcode rc;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m783[0m[39m:  bool removed_timer = FALSE;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m784[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m785[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* First, make some basic checks that the CURLM handle is a good handle *[0m[35m/[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m786[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mGOOD_MULTI_HANDLE[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmulti[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m787[0m[39m:    return CURLM_BAD_HANDLE;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m788[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m789[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Verify that we got a somewhat good easy handle too *[0m[35m/[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m790[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mGOOD_EASY_HANDLE[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || !multi->num_easy[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m791[0m[39m:    return CURLM_BAD_EASY_HANDLE;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m792[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m793[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Prevent users from trying to remove same easy handle more than once *[0m[35m/[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m794[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!data->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m795[0m[39m:    return CURLM_OK; [0m[35m/[0m[39m* it is already removed so let's say it is fine! *[0m[35m/[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The AddressSanitizer crash in `Curl_doh_close` is caused by recursive cleanup of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe same DoH context [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`data->req.doh`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when closing each probe’s easy handle. Each [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprobe’s `[0m[1;35mCurl_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` invokes `Curl_req_done` → `Curl_doh_close` again [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mon the probe handle, whose `req.doh` still points at the parent DoH context. This [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msecond invocation walks the same `doh->probe` array—some entries have already been [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreset—and ultimately reads from or frees the stale `doh` memory, resulting in a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwild-addr-read.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Critical Logic to Preserve  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We must still iterate all `DOH_SLOT_COUNT` probes on the main handle to [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleanly remove them from the multi-handle and perform full easy-handle teardown.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We must not alter any multi- or easy-handle removal sequence, and we must not [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodify the fuzzing harness or tests.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Strategy  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In `lib/doh.c`, function `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, locate the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloop over all `doh->probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` entries around line [0m[1;36m1409[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m1417[0m[39m.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Immediately before calling `[0m[1;35mCurl_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, nullify the probe [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandle’s DoH context pointer to prevent recursive DoH cleanup on that handle. [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mConcretely:  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```diff[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[39m* [0m[33m...[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           continue;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* data->multi might already be reset at this time *[0m[35m/[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-        [0m[1;35mcurl_multi_remove_handle[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->multi, probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-        [0m[1;35mCurl_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* data->multi might already be reset at this time *[0m[35m/[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[1;35mcurl_multi_remove_handle[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->multi, probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Prevent the probe’s own teardown from re-running Curl_doh_close: *[0m[35m/[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        probe_data->req.doh = NULL;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[1;35mCurl_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Leave the parent handle’s `data->req.doh` intact. The final free of the DoH [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontext occurs in the normal cleanup path [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `Curl_doh_cleanup` during [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`curl_easy_cleanup`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and will run once.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Why This Works  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By nullifying `probe_data->req.doh`, the probe-specific easy handle’s [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubsequent `Curl_req_done` → `Curl_doh_close` call short-circuits immediately [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. This eliminates the recursive walk of `doh->probe`, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreventing double-use of the same memory and avoiding the invalid read.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We perform this change only in the source under `lib/doh.c`, preserving all [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting multi and easy-handle teardown behavior for non-DoH code.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We do not touch the harness, fuzzing logic, or tests.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects & Mitigations  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Risk: If probe handles legitimately needed to perform any DoH cleanup of their[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mown separate state, this patch fully suppresses `Curl_doh_close` for them. However,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprobe handles do not manage independent DoH state—they share the parent context—so [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msuppressing their DoH cleanup is correct.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We retain parent-context cleanup in the normal `curl_easy_cleanup` path, so no[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemory leak or dangling pointer remains for the DoH context.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We have limited the change to a single line per loop iteration, minimizing [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrisk to unaffected code paths.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. No Further Changes Needed  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   All other code in `lib/request.c`, `lib/multi.c`, and the fuzz harness remains [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalid. This targeted fix preserves existing functionality while eliminating the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrash.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m[12/28/25 12:01:26][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.EVALUATE -> TeamStatus.ANALYZE                  ]8;id=250844;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=703286;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\

[2;36m[12/28/25 12:03:38][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.[1;33mPATCH[0m -> TeamStatus.EVALUATE                    ]8;id=138046;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=183491;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer `curl_fuzzer_http` triggers a segmentation fault in `Curl_doh_close` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1410[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when running a single input [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m times. The initial crash stack [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtraces through `Curl_req_done`, `multi_done`, `multi_runsingle`, [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`curl_multi_perform`, into the fuzzer harness. An attempted patch in `lib/doh.c` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madds a nulling of `probe_data->req.doh` immediately after [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`curl_multi_remove_handle` and before `Curl_close`. After applying the patch, the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame crash at line [0m[1;36m1410[0m[39m in `Curl_doh_close` still occurs, indicating the patch did [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot prevent the invalid read.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - When the fuzzer runs `[0m[35m/out/[0m[95mcurl_fuzzer_http[0m[39m` with a test case, [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer reports a READ of an invalid address in `Curl_doh_close` [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mdoh.[0m[1;92mc:1410:30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack backtrace:  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Curl_doh_close [0m[1;39m([0m[35m/src/curl/lib/[0m[95mdoh.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m1410[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Curl_req_done [0m[1;39m([0m[35m/src/curl/lib/[0m[95mrequest.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m108[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. multi_done [0m[1;39m([0m[35m/src/curl/lib/[0m[95mmulti.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m754[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. multi_runsingle [0m[1;39m([0m[35m/src/curl/lib/[0m[95mmulti.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m2856[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. curl_multi_perform [0m[1;39m([0m[35m/src/curl/lib/[0m[95mmulti.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;36m3016[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. fuzz_handle_transfer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurl_fuzzer.[0m[1;92mcc:419[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m. LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcurl_fuzzer.[0m[1;92mcc:97[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The harness code invokes the multi-interface loop, ultimately calling [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_req_done`, which calls `Curl_doh_close`.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Observations in Initial Log  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The invalid read is caused by dereferencing a “high value address,” suggesting[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma stale or uninitialized pointer within the DOH request structure.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash consistently occurs in `Curl_doh_close` when cleaning up DOH [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minternal state.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Location: in `lib/doh.c`, immediately after calling [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mcurl_multi_remove_handle[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->multi, probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Addition:  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mcurl_multi_remove_handle[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->multi, probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+      probe_data->req.doh = NULL;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mCurl_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Intent: clear the `doh` pointer before the subsequent `Curl_close` call to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevent `Curl_doh_close` from operating on invalid data.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Result After Patch  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The same AddressSanitizer crash occurs at `lib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1410[0m[39m` in `Curl_doh_close`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munder identical conditions.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack trace and crash location are unchanged, indicating the pointer nulling [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdid not intercept the faulty code path or the crash happens earlier than the null [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39massignment.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The lifecycle and initialization of `data->req.doh` in the DOH code path, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincluding where it is allocated, assigned, and freed.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Conditions under which `multi_done` calls into `Curl_doh_close`, especially [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen `data->multi` has already been reset or when `probe_data` fields have [0m         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash occurs in Curl_doh_close when `Curl_req_done` is invoked on “probe” [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39measy handles created for DoH lookups [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doh_run_probe`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. These probe handles never [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocate `data->req.doh`, so its pointer remains NULL or uninitialized. Yet [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_req_done` unconditionally calls `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which dereferences [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh` and causes a wild-address read.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Core Insight[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Only handles that went through the DoH resolution setup [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Curl_doh`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m have a [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalid `data->req.doh` pointer. Probe handles should never enter `Curl_doh_close`. [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mGuarding the call in `Curl_req_done` based on the presence of a non-NULL [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh` field prevents invalid access without affecting the regular DoH [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleanup path.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Steps[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Open lib/request.c and locate the `Curl_req_done` function [0m[1;39m([0m[39mroughly lines [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m111[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Replace the unconditional invocation of `Curl_doh_close` with a NULL-check [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguard:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```diff[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      --- a/lib/request.c[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      +++ b/lib/request.c[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      @@ [0m[1;36m-106[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m106[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m9[0m[39m @@ CURLcode [0m[1;35mCurl_req_done[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct SingleRequest *req,[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mCurl_client_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      -  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      +  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Only close DoH state if it was actually allocated *[0m[35m/[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      +  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      +    [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #endif[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return CURLE_OK;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. No changes to any harness, fuzzing logic, or external libraries.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. No changes to test code; all existing tests and fuzz targets remain valid.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Functionality[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Main easy handles that initiated a DoH lookup will have `data->req.doh != [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNULL`. They will still enter `Curl_doh_close` and free their DoH probes as before.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Probe handles [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhere `doh_run_probe` creates one-off easy handles for [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDNS-over-HTTPS queries[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m do _not_ allocate `data->req.doh`. They bypass [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close`, avoiding the invalid dereference. Their lifecycle is otherwise [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munaffected by this guard.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Side Effects and Mitigations[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - There is a small risk that a future code path might allocate `data->req.doh` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlate or reassign it; however, all current DoH setup is done up-front in `Curl_doh`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mso this guard is safe.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `data->req.doh` is not reset by `Curl_doh_close` itself. Since `Curl_req_done`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly happens once per handle, and the easy handle is destroyed immediately [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mafterward, the dangling pointer does not persist or cause double-free.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If in the future `Curl_doh_close` is called elsewhere, developers should [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensure similar guarding or inside `Curl_doh_close` reset the pointer. But for the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcurrent crash scenario, guarding in `Curl_req_done` fully addresses the issue.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Why This Is Optimal[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Minimalistic: touches a single if-condition in a central cleanup function.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Non-intrusive: avoids any modifications to the DoH probe logic, `curl_multi` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minternals, or fuzz harness.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Correctly scopes cleanup to only those handles with real DoH state, [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meliminating the wild read with zero behavioral change for valid flows.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mirrors patterns elsewhere in libcurl where resource-specific cleanup is [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguarded by checking the associated pointer or flag.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. No Further File Retrieval Needed[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The necessary context for the patch resides entirely within lib/request.c and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mknowledge of how `data->req.doh` is initialized in lib/doh.c. No additional code [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths need inspection for this fix.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer uncovered a segmentation fault in the DoH cleanup function [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close` when running `curl_fuzzer_http`. A patch was applied to guard the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall to `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in `lib/request.c` so it only executes when [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh` is non-null. After rebuilding and rerunning the fuzzer, the crash [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstill occurs at the same location in `Curl_doh_close`.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A libFuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`curl_fuzzer_http`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m exercising HTTP and DNS-over-HTTPS [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDoH[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Type: SEGV on unknown address [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwild-addr-read[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Crash site: Curl_doh_close at lib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1410:30[0m[39m  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Stack trace highlights the call chain:  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Curl_doh_close  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Curl_req_done [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlib/request.[0m[1;92mc:108[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Original snippet in `[0m[1;35mCurl_req_done[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```c[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  #endif[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```c[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This guard intends to skip calling the cleanup function when no DoH state exists.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m479[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/request.[0m[1;92mc:100[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m111[0m                                                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m105[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvoid[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35mreq_flush[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m106[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_client_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m107[0m[39m:#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m108[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m109[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m110[0m[39m:  return CURLE_OK;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m111[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1431[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1440[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1431[0m[39m:void [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1432[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1433[0m[39m:  struct doh_probes *doh = data->req.doh;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1434[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1435[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1436[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1437[0m[39m:    data->req.doh->req_hds = NULL;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1438[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1439[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1440[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The segmentation fault in `Curl_doh_close` stems from `data->req.doh` pointing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto freed or uninitialized memory.  The existing code calls `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat request completion but never frees the `doh_probes` struct nor nullifies [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh`.  A subsequent call to `Curl_doh_close` thus operates on invalid [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemory, leading to a wild read in `doh->probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The one-line guard patch [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m did not [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhelp because `data->req.doh` remained non-NULL even after the first close, pointing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat freed memory.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Preservation of Critical Logic:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We must continue to invoke the DoH-close logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcancelling any ongoing probes [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand removing them from the multi handle[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We must not alter the fuzzing harness or multi interface logic.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We must not delete DoH support entirely.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Outline:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In `lib/request.c`, locate the function `Curl_req_done` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround lines [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m111[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Replace the direct call to `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor its guarded [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvariant[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with a call to `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - `Curl_doh_cleanup` internally:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Calls `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` if `data->req.doh` is non-NULL.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Frees the associated header list `req_hds`.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `[0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and sets `data->req.doh` to NULL.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - By invoking `Curl_doh_cleanup`, we both run the proper close logic and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrelease the underlying memory, preventing dangling pointers.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Remove or simplify any conditional guard around the cleanup call, since [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_cleanup` itself checks for a non-NULL `req.doh`.  [0m[1;39m([0m[39mRetaining an outer [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is optional but not strictly necessary.[0m[1;39m)[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Detailed Steps:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Open `lib/request.c`.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Find:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     CURLcode [0m[1;35mCurl_req_done[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct SingleRequest *req,[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                            struct Curl_easy *data, bool aborted[0m[1;39m)[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[33m...[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* old code *[0m[35m/[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-      [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   #endif[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[33m...[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replace that block with:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Close and free DoH state to avoid dangling pointers *[0m[35m/[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   #endif[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Save and rebuild.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Justification:[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `Curl_doh_cleanup` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1431[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m1440[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m encapsulates both the close and free [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msteps:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     void [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       struct doh_probes *doh = data->req.doh;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         data->req.doh->req_hds = NULL;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This ensures that after each request completes, the DoH state is not only [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclosed but also deallocated, and the pointer reset to NULL.  Future invocations of [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhether in the same handle or in `Curl_close`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will see [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`data->req.doh == NULL` and exit immediately, preventing wild reads.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The existing request-flow and multi-interface logic remain untouched, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreserving all current functionality.  Tests and fuzz harnesses continue to drive [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe same code paths; only the cleanup is hardened.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects & Mitigations:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Because `Curl_doh_cleanup` also frees `req_hds`, ensure no code later in the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame request relies on those headers after `Curl_req_done`.  As this is [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mend-of-request cleanup, there are no remaining users of the DoH state.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Calling `Curl_doh_cleanup` twice is safe: the second call sees `data->req.doh [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== NULL` and returns immediately.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No extra allocations or performance regressions are introduced—just proper [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeallocation.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Conclusion:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   By replacing the bare `Curl_doh_close` invocation with `Curl_doh_cleanup`, we [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meliminate dangling `data->req.doh` pointers across request boundaries.  This [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectly addresses the ASan-reported wild address read in `Curl_doh_close` without [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtouching harness code, external libraries, or tests.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
