[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe OSS-Fuzz harness for curl’s HTTP fuzzer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`curl_fuzzer_http`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m triggers a [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msegmentation fault inside the DNS-over-HTTPS cleanup routine [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Curl_doh_close`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen running a single testcase. The initial backtrace shows a wild-memory read in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close` called from `Curl_req_done` → `multi_done` → `curl_multi_perform`.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA patch was attempted in `lib/request.c`, replacing the call to [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in `Curl_req_done`. After [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrebuilding and re-running the fuzzer, the same sanitizer error reappears: the crash[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstill lands in `Curl_doh_close` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnow called internally by `Curl_doh_cleanup`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, with[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man almost identical backtrace shifted by one stack frame.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer is invoked via libFuzzer in “interactive” mode, running [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m input [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimes.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- On the first run with `[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`, AddressSanitizer reports:  [0m                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Caused by a READ of a high-value address [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwild-addr-read[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Crash location: `Curl_doh_close` in `lib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1410:30[0m[39m`.  [0m                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1408[0m[39m:    size_t slot;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1409[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mfor[0m[1;39m([0m[39mslot = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; slot < DOH_SLOT_COUNT; slot++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1410[0m[39m:      mid = doh->probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.easy_mid;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1411[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmid < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1412[0m[39m:        continue;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1413[0m[39m:      doh->probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.easy_mid = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1414[0m[39m:      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* should have been called before data is removed from multi handle *[0m[35m/[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1415[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mDEBUGASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1416[0m[39m:      probe_data = data->multi ? [0m[1;35mCurl_multi_get_handle[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->multi, mid[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m :[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1417[0m[39m:        NULL;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1418[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1419[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mDEBUGF[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35minfof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, [0m[32m"Curl_doh_close: xfer for [0m[32mmid[0m[32m=%"[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1420[0m[39m:                     FMT_OFF_T [0m[32m" not found!"[0m[39m,[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1421[0m[39m:                     doh->probe[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mslot[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.easy_mid[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1422[0m[39m:        continue;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1425[0m[39m:      [0m[1;35mcurl_multi_remove_handle[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->multi, probe_data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m751[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mprocess_pending_handles[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[35m/[0m[39m* connection [0m[35m/[0m[39m multiplex *[0m[35m/[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m752[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m753[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!result[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m754[0m[39m:    result = [0m[1;35mCurl_req_done[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&data->req, data, premature[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/multi.[0m[1;92mc:748[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m756[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m748[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Inform connection filters that this transfer is done *[0m[35m/[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m749[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_conn_ev_data_done[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, premature[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m750[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m751[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mprocess_pending_handles[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[35m/[0m[39m* connection [0m[35m/[0m[39m multiplex *[0m[35m/[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m752[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m753[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!result[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m754[0m[39m:    result = [0m[1;35mCurl_req_done[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&data->req, data, premature[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m755[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m756[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Under the potential connection pool's share lock, decide what to[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/multi.[0m[1;92mc:822[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m830[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m822[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->conn[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m823[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* [0m[1;35mmulti_done[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m clears the association between the easy handle and the[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m824[0m[39m:       connection.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m825[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m826[0m[39m:       Note that this ignores the return code simply because there is[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m827[0m[39m:       nothing really useful to do with it anyway! *[0m[35m/[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m828[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvoid[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35mmulti_done[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, data->result, premature[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m829[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m830[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/doh.[0m[1;92mc:1431[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1438[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1431[0m[39m:void [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1432[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1433[0m[39m:  struct doh_probes *doh = data->req.doh;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1434[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1435[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1436[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1437[0m[39m:    data->req.doh->req_hds = NULL;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1438[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->req.doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The segmentation fault arises because the DNS-over-HTTPS [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDOH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m state [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`data->req.doh`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is cleaned up twice and its pointer never reset to NULL.  On the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfirst cleanup [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `Curl_req_done`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, we now call `Curl_doh_cleanup`, which frees the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`doh_probes` struct but leaves the dangling pointer in `data->req.doh`.  Later, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen `Curl_req_free` or a second `Curl_req_done` runs, it again invokes [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleanup/close on the freed structure, causing a wild-memory read in [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_doh_close`.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Changes  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m In `lib/request.c`, ensure that request completion invokes the full DOH [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleanup [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnot just the close loop[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m In `lib/doh.c`, modify `Curl_doh_cleanup` so that after freeing the [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`doh_probes` struct, we set `data->req.doh = NULL`.  This prevents any subsequent [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalls from operating on freed memory.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Outline  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m lib/request.c  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Around the end of `Curl_req_done`, replace the old `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - [0m[1;39m([0m[39mThis may already be in place from the prior patch.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m lib/doh.c  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - In `[0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, change the cleanup block:  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       * Use the local `doh` pointer to free the header list and the struct itself.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       * **After** `[0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`, set `data->req.doh = NULL;`.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This yields a one‐time cleanup: after the first invocation, `data->req.doh` is [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNULL and further calls to `Curl_doh_close` or `Curl_doh_cleanup` are no‐ops.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Why This Works  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By zeroing out `data->req.doh` after the first free, we eliminate the dangling[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer.  Any subsequent `Curl_doh_close` will see a NULL pointer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mskipping its [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloop entirely[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and any subsequent `Curl_doh_cleanup` will immediately return.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We preserve the existing logic:  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * The DOH probe handles are still removed in `Curl_doh_close`.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * The header list is freed exactly once.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * The `doh_probes` struct is freed exactly once.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We do **not** alter any fuzzing harness or test code.  We only adjust DOH [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mteardown in the library so that no stale pointers remain across multiple requests. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In normal [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnon‐fuzz[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m usage, DOH state may be reused across multiple requests [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mon the same handle.  This patch causes DOH state to be torn down at the end of [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m*every* request [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia `Curl_req_done`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  However, this aligns with the original [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintent of calling `Curl_doh_close` on each request completion and then fully [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfreeing the state at handle cleanup.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Downstream code that expected to call `Curl_doh_cleanup` only once [0m[1;39m([0m[39min [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Curl_req_free`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will still find an intact pointer the first time and a NULL [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer the second time—behaviorally equivalent to “cleanup only once.”  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Detailed Steps to Apply  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. In lib/request.c, ensure the end of `Curl_req_done` reads:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       #endif  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. In lib/doh.c, edit `Curl_doh_cleanup` to:[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       void [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         struct doh_probes *doh = data->req.doh;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!doh[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           return;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         doh->req_hds = NULL;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;           [0m[35m/[0m[39m* frees the doh_probes struct *[0m[35m/[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         data->req.doh = NULL;         [0m[35m/[0m[39m* reset the pointer to avoid dangling *[0m[35m/[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Rebuild and re-run the HTTP fuzzer.  The sanitizer should no longer report [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwild-memory reads in `Curl_doh_close`.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Verification  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm that on both the first and subsequent fuzz iterations, `data->req.doh`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis always either a valid pointer during DOH operation or NULL before/after cleanup.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Observe that `Curl_doh_close` is never invoked on a freed `doh_probes` struct.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing tests and harnesses [0m[1;39m([0m[39mincluding the HTTP fuzzer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pass without [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodification.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m103[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvoid[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mreq;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m104[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!aborted[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m105[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvoid[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35mreq_flush[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m106[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_client_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m107[0m[39m:#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m108[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m109[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m110[0m[39m:  return CURLE_OK;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m111[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/request.[0m[1;92mc:170[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m183[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m170[0m[39m:void [0m[1;35mCurl_req_free[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct SingleRequest *req, struct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m171[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m172[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* This is a bit ugly. `req->p` is a union and we assume we can[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m173[0m[39m:   * free this safely without leaks. *[0m[35m/[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m174[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mreq->p.ftp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m175[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mreq->newurl[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m176[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mreq->sendbuf_init[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m177[0m[39m:    [0m[1;35mCurl_bufq_free[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&req->sendbuf[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m178[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_client_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m179[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m180[0m[39m:#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m181[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m182[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m183[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/multi.[0m[1;92mc:748[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m754[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m748[0m[39m:  [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Inform connection filters that this transfer is done *[0m[35m/[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m749[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_conn_ev_data_done[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, premature[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m750[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m751[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mprocess_pending_handles[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->multi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[35m/[0m[39m* connection [0m[35m/[0m[39m multiplex *[0m[35m/[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m752[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m753[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!result[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m754[0m[39m:    result = [0m[1;35mCurl_req_done[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&data->req, data, premature[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlib/request.[0m[1;92mc:100[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m111[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m100:C[0m[39mURLcode [0m[1;35mCurl_req_done[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct SingleRequest *req,[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m101[0m[39m:                       struct Curl_easy *data, bool aborted[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m102[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m103[0m[39m:  [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvoid[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mreq;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m104[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!aborted[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m105[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvoid[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35mreq_flush[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m106[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_client_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m107[0m[39m:#ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m108[0m[39m:  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m109[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m110[0m[39m:  return CURLE_OK;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m111[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root cause analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer crash is a wild‐address read inside [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, triggered [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbecause data->req.doh points to a struct whose internal pointers [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnotably req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare uninitialized garbage.  Although [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m now checks for [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata->req.doh != NULL, it still calls [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m on a partially or [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mun‐initialized doh_probes, leading to invalid memory dereferences.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The code path that allocates and initializes struct doh_probes does not [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mzero‐initialize all pointer fields.  As a result, even though data->req.doh itself [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis set, its req_hds [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand possibly other members[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m contain indeterminate values.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWhen deregistering/resolving DOH, [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m blindly walks/free’s those [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointers, causing the wild read.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replacing [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with a cleanup wrapper in Curl_req_done was correct[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto unify full cleanup, but it did not address the underlying need for doh_probes to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe fully initialized before use.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Additionally, [0m[1;35mCurl_client_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcalled just before Curl_req_done[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m resets [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmany per‐request fields but does not touch data->req.doh, leaving it dangling [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39macross requests until the explicit cleanup calls.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. High‐level fix approach[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Ensure that when a new struct doh_probes is allocated or assigned [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi.e., in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe DOH init path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, all its pointer members are initialized to safe NULL values.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis prevents [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m from ever dereferencing an uninitialized pointer.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Strengthen [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m check and free req_hds only if it is non‐NULL,[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m avoid calling [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m if the doh_probes struct was never fully [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minitialized,[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m3[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m then free the struct and null out data->req.doh.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. In [0m[1;35mCurl_req_done[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, continue using [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnot [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto ensure no stale doh_probes is left, but rely on the improved initialization and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguards in cleanup to avoid wild reads.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. Optionally [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefensive[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: add `data->req.doh = NULL` in [0m[1;35mCurl_client_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m so [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat if a request is aborted mid‐init before a doh_probes is set up, it cannot be [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mseen as non‐NULL in req_done.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed patch outline[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. lib/doh.c: struct doh_probes allocation[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Locate the code path where data->req.doh = [0m[1;35mmalloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39msizeof *doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe DOH setup function[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Change that to either use [0m[1;35mcalloc[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or explicitly:[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         doh = [0m[1;35mmalloc[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35mmemset[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, sizeof *doh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - This zeroes req_hds and all other pointer fields.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. lib/doh.c: strengthen Curl_doh_cleanup[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      void [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct Curl_easy *data[0m[1;39m)[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        struct doh_probes *doh = data->req.doh;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!doh[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Only call Curl_doh_close if the doh->curl handle [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor another[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           core field[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m was fully initialized. *[0m[35m/[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->curl[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Free any header list if it exists *[0m[35m/[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mif[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mcurl_slist_free_all[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh->req_hds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          doh->req_hds = NULL;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Free the struct and null the pointer *[0m[35m/[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mCurl_safefree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoh[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        data->req.doh = NULL;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Note: Checking doh->curl [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor another dedicated “initialized” flag[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m prevents[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m on a half‐initialized doh_probes.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. lib/request.c: Curl_req_done[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Keep the existing replacement of [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mso that we get the full guarded teardown rather than the raw close.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```diff[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #ifndef CURL_DISABLE_DOH[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      -  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      +  [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #endif[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. lib/client.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39moptional defensive change[0m[1;39m)[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In [0m[1;35mCurl_client_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, after resetting other per‐request fields, add:[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        `data->req.doh = NULL;`[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - This ensures that if a DOH init was never completed in this request cycle, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreq_done cannot see a stale pointer.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Zero‐initializing doh_probes eliminates all “wild” pointers in its members, so[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the new cleanup wrapper will never touch uninitialized memory.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Guarding the call to [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m on a concrete flag [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. doh->curl[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevents invoking internal cleanup logic on a partially set‐up struct.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Unifying all per‐request DOH cleanup behind [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_cleanup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCurl_req_done and in Curl_req_free ensures consistent teardown logic.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adding a defensive reset of data->req.doh to NULL in [0m[1;35mCurl_client_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevents races where an abort or partial pathway leaves a non‐NULL but invalid [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Preserving existing logic and tests[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No external libraries or fuzzing harness code are modified.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - DOH teardown logic is now stricter but still calls [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m where [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mappropriate and always frees the header list and struct exactly once.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Tests that perform multiple requests with DOH enabled will observe the same [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbehavior but without wild reads or crashes.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Backward‐compatibility: if older code relied on [0m[1;35mCurl_doh_close[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to free [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreq_hds, the wrapper still frees it if doh->curl was set, so behavior is preserved.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Side‐effects and mitigation[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Minor code-size increase by adding explicit initializers and guards.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The optional data->req.doh reset in [0m[1;35mCurl_client_reset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m could mask logic that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpected doh to survive a `[0m[1;35mreq_flush[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` step.  However, since `req_free` and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`req_done` now both use cleanup, this is safe.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Comprehensive test: fuzzing with AddressSanitizer to ensure no wild reads [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremain.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
